   "fix": "State `IsComplexLinearMap (J) (J') (F : V \u2192\u2097[\u211d] W) : Prop` on plain linear maps, then write `IsComplexLinearMap J J' f'.toLinearMap` (or a CLM-specialized abbreviation) inside `IsJHolomorphicAt` etc. The derivative is still a CLM where used, but the predicate becomes usable for non-continuous/algebraic linear maps.",
